						<summary>

						<p>Stone lying in the dilapidated site of the Gōpālasvāmin temple outside the village.</p>						

						<p>Sadāśivadēva, 1561 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1483, Durmati Chaitra ba. 10</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1561 A.D., April 9, Wednesday.</hi></p>						

						<p>Damaged and worn out. Seems to refer to some gifts made by Timmarāju.</p>						

						</summary>
